; Git LFS endpoint override.
;
; The kbve monorepo lives on GitHub; large binary assets are stored on
; the self-hosted Forgejo instance at git.kbve.com. Each game's
; binaries live in their own LFS-only repo under the KBVE org:
;   KBVE/chuck      → Unreal artifact repo
;   KBVE/rareicon   → Unity artifact repo (configured below)
;
; Pointer files land in this repo (small text); blobs land on Forgejo
; over HTTPS. git.kbve.com routes through ingress-nginx (.74) instead
; of the Cilium gateway (.71) because Cloudflare's path to .71 hits
; 522 origin-timeouts on the LFS batch endpoint while .74 is reached
; cleanly. The nginx ingress disables proxy-body-size and stretches
; upstream timeouts so multi-hundred-MB pushes don't get cut off.
;
; Devs touching apps/rareicon/**/Plugins/** need a Forgejo account
; with a personal access token (or basic auth) the first time they
; push; `git lfs push` will prompt and credentials are cached by the
; system credential helper. Devs working elsewhere in the monorepo
; never invoke the LFS smudge filter and can ignore Forgejo entirely
; (clone with GIT_LFS_SKIP_SMUDGE=1 to skip the smudge round-trip if
; `git lfs` isn't installed locally).
[lfs]
    url = https://git.kbve.com/KBVE/rareicon.git/info/lfs
